# docker/.env.example
#
# Copy to docker/.env on the 4070 host. The real .env file is gitignored
# because the bind host is a per-host operational fact (Tailscale IP)
# rather than something that belongs in version control.
#
# Sprint 3c: the brainstem's published port is restricted to this host
# interface. On the 4070, set it to the host's Tailscale IPv4 address
# (the result of `tailscale ip -4`). On a developer laptop without a
# Tailscale install, leave it unset and Docker will default to
# 127.0.0.1 via the compose file's ${BRAINSTEM_BIND_HOST:-127.0.0.1}
# expansion.
#
# To refresh after a Tailscale IP rotation:
#   scripts/setup/refresh-tailscale-bind.ps1
#
# See docs/exposure_and_cortex_down.md for the full design.

BRAINSTEM_BIND_HOST=<REDACTED_TAILSCALE_IP>
